					<img alt='' src='http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/acd89a6d54c9c1513318eaaafd990d8c?s=48&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=G' class='author-profile-pic avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />	
					<cite class=\"comment-author\">
						<a href='' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Michael Franklin</a>					</cite>
				</div>
					
				<p>There is, of course, the issue of trust&#8230; and that leaves the media/press without much to work with. News is not reported for the sake of the people or information but for how much profit that can be generated from it. It should also be noted that in some societies, the media is a tool of government or corporate policy makers so&#8230; what gets printed is what is approved without regard to fact.</p>
